# Phase-1 freeze (stable — do not redesign)

These modules are **complete and production-stable**. Do not redesign, refactor, or change behavior unless fixing a **verified bug**.

| Module | Scope (avoid unless bugfix) |
|--------|-----------------------------|
| Vehicle Registration | `components/owner/vehicles/`, `VehicleListingWizard`, `VehicleServiceAvailabilityFields`, `server/actions/vehicles.ts` (create/edit/KYC gates) |
| Owner / Customer Approval | Admin approval flows, `marketplace-gates`, owner KYC approval |
| Search | `lib/supabase/queries.ts` (`searchDriverVehicles`, `searchSelfDriveVehicles`, `searchReturnJourneys`, `fetchDriverSearchVehicles`), `lib/vehicles/driver-search-filter.ts`, `components/search/`, `app/search-*`, `app/api/search-*` |
| Vehicle Rendering | Search result cards, vehicle display on search pages |
| Service Types | `lib/vehicles/services.ts`, `service_*` columns, service badges |
| Trip Types | `lib/vehicles/trip-types.ts`, `trip_*` columns |

**Before editing any file**, check whether it touches search or vehicle registration. If yes, stop unless the task is an explicit bugfix for that module.

**Shared files** (e.g. `queries.ts`, `types/database.ts`): change only what booking needs; do not alter search filter logic or vehicle listing behavior.

---

# Phase-2: Booking workflow (active development)

Work **one module at a time**, in this order. Keep the app production-ready (build passes, no regressions in frozen modules).

1. Booking Review
2. Rider Authentication
3. Payment
4. Booking Confirmation
5. My Bookings
6. Cancellation
7. Refund
8. Owner Earnings
9. Wallet
10. Notifications

Prefer minimal, focused diffs. Reuse existing booking/payment/auth code. Do not re-open search or vehicle registration unless a booking bug requires a surgical fix.
